    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "71d1e4ce_b8e2570a",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/cmd/tast/internal/run/run_tests.go",
        "patchSetId": 10
      },
      "lineNbr": 171,
      "author": {
        "id": 1431492
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-13T23:03:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I was trying to make the first few tests has one extra test when the number of tests is not divisible by the number of shards. I did that way because I think it is easier for the user to figure out the number of tests for each shard.\n\nLet\u0027s look at the the case that the number of tests is 10 and the number of shards is 4. \n\nFor the current implementation, the start and end index for each index:\n\nShard Index    Start Index    End Index\n     0             0             3\n     1             3             6\n     2             6             8\n     3             8            10\n\nThe first and second shard have 3 tests each. The third and fourth shard have 2 tests each.\n\nWith the formula:\n startIndex :\u003d numTests * shardIndex / totalShards\n endIndex :\u003d numTests * (shardIndex + 1) / totalShards\n\nThis would be the values:\nShard Index    Start Index    End Index\n     0             0             2 \u003d 10 * (0 + 1) / 4\n     1             2             5 \u003d 10 * (1 + 1) / 4\n     2             5             7 \u003d 10 * (2 + 1) / 4\n     3             7            10 \u003d 10 * (3 + 1) / 4\n\nThe first and third test have 2 tests each. The second and the fourth have 3 tests each.\n\nPlease let me know if you still want the change. Thanks.",
      "parentUuid": "2f16b332_5abf83ba",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 133,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 171,
        "endChar": 1
      },
      "revId": "0ca5f5ed57639db3130aa3b283843d9672fb98e0",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
